parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor visibility of the instrument cluster, particularly during daylight hours, can cause drivers to take their eyes off the road for extended periods, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: inability to see gauge markings during the day
and unreadable gauges in shaded or overcast conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Charge Pipe Failure at Throttle Body Clamp
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the charge pipe can cause a loss of power, leading to potential safety risks, especially when merging onto a freeway or taking a left turn.
symptoms: broken parts of the charge pipe falling onto the undertray
check engine light coming on after a delay.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced visibility of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, engine RPM, and other critical vehicle information, increasing the risk of accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: and other instrument cluster gauges during daytime driving
glare or reflection on the instrument cluster
inability to see critical vehicle information.
